1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,009
Big thinkers train themselves to see not just what is, but what can be.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:08,529
Here are four examples to illustrate this point.

3
00:00:08,529 --> 00:00:09,889
1.

4
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:12,690
What gives real estate value?

5
00:00:12,960 --> 00:00:24,210
A highly successful realtor who specializes in rural property shows what can be done if we train ourselves to see something where little or nothing presently exists.

6
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:31,810
Most of the rural property around here, my friend began, is run down and not very attractive.

7
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:37,570
I'm successful because I don't try to sell my prospects a farm as it is.

8
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:42,450
I develop my entire sales plan around what the farm can be.

9
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:51,810
Simply telling the prospect, the farm has XX acres of bottom land and XX acres of woods and is XX miles from town,

10
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,610
doesn't stir him up and make him want to buy it.

11
00:00:54,800 --> 00:01:00,690
But when you show him a concrete plan for doing something with the farm, he's just about sold.

12
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:03,250
Here, let me show you what I mean.

13
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:06,690
He opened his briefcase and pulled out a file.

14
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:10,850
This farm," he said, is a new listing with us.

15
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:12,289
It's like a lot of them.

16
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:17,810
It's forty-three miles from the center of the metropolitan area, the house is run down,

17
00:01:17,810 --> 00:01:20,610
and the place hasn't been farmed in five years.

18
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:22,370
Now here's what I've done.

19
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:27,170
I spent two full days on the place last week, just studying it.

20
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:29,570
I walked over the place several times.

21
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:31,570
I looked at neighboring farms.

22
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:36,850
I studied the location of the farm with respect to existing and planned highways.

23
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:40,210
I asked myself, what's this farm good for?

24
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:43,009
I came up with three possibilities.

25
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,050
Here they are.

26
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:45,649
He showed them to me.

27
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:49,649
Each plan was neatly typed and looked quite comprehensive.

28
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,970
One plan suggested converting the farm into a riding stable.

29
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:56,850
The plan showed why the idea was sound.

30
00:01:56,960 --> 00:02:02,610
A growing city, more love for the outdoors, more money for recreation, good roads.

31
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:07,490
The plan also showed how the farm could support a sizable number of horses,

32
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:10,850
so that the revenue from the rides would be largely clear.

33
00:02:11,040 --> 00:02:15,250
The whole riding stable idea was very thorough, very convincing.

34
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:22,610
The plan was so clear and convincing, I could see a dozen couples riding horseback through the trees.

35
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:33,649
In similar fashion, this enterprising salesman developed a second thorough plan for a tree farm and a third plan for a combination tree and poultry farm.

36
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:40,769
Now, when I talk with my prospects, I won't have to convince them that the farm is a good buy as it is.

37
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:45,970
I help them to see a picture of the farm changed into a money-making proposition.

38
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:54,610
Besides selling more farms and selling them faster, my method of selling the property for what it can be pays off in another way.

39
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:58,610
I can sell a farm at a higher price than my competitors.

40
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:04,529
People naturally pay more for acreage and an idea than they do for just acreage.

41
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:11,410
Because of this, more people want to list their farms with me and my commission on each sale is larger.

42
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,730
The moral is this.

43
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:17,809
Look at things not as they are, but as they can be.

44
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:20,930
Visualization adds value to everything.

